From: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott@hotmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7996: Stop tx_free parsing at the buffer edge

AN7581 NPU tx_free descriptors can report an MSDU count that reaches the skb
boundary. Stop at the real boundary while still releasing entries already
collected from the descriptor.

Signed-off-by: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott@hotmail.com>
---
--- a/mt7996/mac.c
+++ b/mt7996/mac.c
@@ -1312,8 +1312,11 @@ mt7996_mac_tx_free(struct mt7996_dev *de
 		u32 msdu, info;
 		u8 i;
 
-		if (WARN_ON_ONCE((void *)cur_info >= end))
-			return;
+		if ((void *)cur_info >= end) {
+			pr_debug("mt7996: tx_free truncated, count=%u total=%u len=%d ver=%u\n",
+				 count, total, len, ver);
+			break;
+		}
 		/* 1'b1: new wcid pair.
 		 * 1'b0: msdu_id with the same 'wcid pair' as above.
 		 */
